column168: UPON INSPECTION OF TWO WET BOXES, RESPONDER DISCOVERED THESE TO BE UNDECLARED DRY ICE PACKAGES WITH CONDENSATION FORMING ON THE OUTSIDE. UPON INSPECTION OF THE INNER CONTENTS DISCOVERED APPROXIMATELY FIVE POUNDS OF DRY ICE COOLING PLANT BASED BURGERS. INNER FLAPS OF THE BOXES HAVE A RED STICKER MARKED PLANTA, CAUTION - DRY ICE - AVOID CONTACT WITH SKIN AND EYES. THESE MARKINGS WERE FOLDED INCORRECTLY SO THEY WERE ONLY VISIBLE WHEN THE BOXES WERE OPENED. THERE WERE NO VISIBLE DRY ICE MARKS OR LABELS ON THE OUTER BOXES. THERE ARE VISIBLE RED STICKERS STATING PLANTA PERISHABLE AND REFRIGERATE UPON ARRIVAL. ADDITIONAL TRACKING NUMBER TO ANOTHER CONSIGNEE IN THE USA IS 1Z25E9F10193762614.
